abstract: Amy B. Fluckiger of Arlington, Va., daughter of Col. Fred Fluckiger, U.S.A., retired, and Mrs. Fluckiger of Richmond, formerly of Hicksville, L.I., was married yesterday afternoon in Springfield, Va., to Charles Hunsaker, son of Mr. and Mrs. Harold Hunsaker of Boca Raton, Fla. The ceremony was performed in St. Mark's Lutheran Church by the pastor, the Rev. Duane Carlson.
headline_main: Charles Hunsaker Marries Amy Fluckiger in Virginia
headline_print_headline: Charles Hunsaker Marries Amy Fluckiger in Virginia

abstract: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. May 30-- The 6,410-yard Wykagyl Country Club course is the longest on the Ladies' Professional Golf Association tour. It also plays as long as most of the United States Women's Open courses, where the length and difficulty are established by the United States Golf Association.

abstract: JACKSONVILLE, Fla., May 27 (AP) Bart Conner of Oklahoma outscored 15 other men tonight to earn the first of six spots on the United States Olympic men's gymnastics team. Tracee Talavera led 21 competitors to gain the top spot on the women's squad.
